title: Fixing a swipe problem, by fixing root cause
message:
Fixing a swipe problem, by fixing root cause

Problem: A swipe is considered a swipe to the top/bottom, while not
allowed to.

Fix: Using the second (and *actual*) solution to the root problem,
mentioned in comment #9735718 in
785ce060dc2b88768a33d579ff615e1e8e2e794f.

title: Fixing notification timing-out while touching
message:
Fixing notification timing-out while touching

Happens while holding a notification and not moving during the specified
time-out duration.
Most noticeable when time-out duration is small, and the notification
has rich content.
In other word, this fix allows "holding" notifications while reading
them.

title: Fixing swipe down when not isShownAtTop
message:
Fixing swipe down when not isShownAtTop

By:
- Defining a new flipped shade background, based on the original shade,
- Removing the background from the container,
- Adding the proper background based on the container position,
- Adding new notifications in the right direction based on the flow,
defined by isShownAtTop.

title: Adding swipe down to hide
message:
Adding swipe down to hide

- Hiding is now set to swiping up if isShownAtTop, and swiping down if
shown at bottom (always swipe to edge to hide).
- Resulted in a new setter in SwipeHelper, for setting swipe direction
when HeadsUpBase is initialized and ready.
- If not isShownAtTop, swiping down will hide, but will also result in a
weird behavior, due to the double-rotation trick.

title: Defining swipe down
message:
Defining swipe down

- New constant: BOTTOM.
- Fix: A gesture is considered a swipe even if the translation = 0.

title: Adding swipe up to hide
message:
Adding swipe up to hide

- Resulted in adding a new constant (TOP) in SwipeHelper.
- The function is implemented without a fading effect, which resulted in
converting FADE_OUT_DURING_SWIPE constant to a variable, and a new
constructor deciding its value (def is true).

title: snapshot of v1.2.4
message:
snapshot of v1.2.4

Version 1.2.4 (18.02.2014)
- Option to use app only while charging
- Option to enable low-priority notifications
- Option to configure timeouts.
- Swipe to dismiss notification
- Fixes for test notification.
- Ability to hide date
- New icon
- Translations (thanks to all who helped me!): Greek, Hebrev, Romanian,
Serbian (cyr.), Arabic, Chinese Simp., Chinese Trad., Dutch, French,
German, Italian, Polish, Portuguese, Brazilian, Slovenian, Spanish,
Swedish
- Some improverments and fixes
